<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1675,2026]" pageId="2" pageNumber="129">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,811,1675,1702]" pageId="2" pageNumber="129">Diagnoses. Male imago. Female imago. Mature Nymph.</emphasis>
As this genus remains monospecific, we expect that the following characteristics may prove to be of importance for specific diagnoses. Therefore, those characteristics used in the generic section can also be used for specific identification.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1675,2026]" pageId="2" pageNumber="129">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,519,1783,1810]" pageId="2" pageNumber="129">Descriptions. Male Imago.</emphasis>
Length: Body 
<quantity box="[695,783,1784,1810]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="2" pageNumber="129" unit="mm" value="2.4">2.4 mm</quantity>
(n=1). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[872,936,1784,1810]" pageId="2" pageNumber="129">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[953,1044,1784,1810]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[218,1363,182,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[208,1379,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Macuxi tunamore gen. nov. sp. nov. imago. A. male, dorsal view; B male, lateral view; C. female, ventral view; D. female, dorsal view; E. male forewing; F. female forewing; G. male genitalia, ventral view; H. detail of posterior margin of subgenital plate (ventral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3629084" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3629084/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="129">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
) black. Turbinate portion of compound eyes brown. Scape, pedicel and flagellum light brown. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[846,935,1820,1846]" pageId="2" pageNumber="129">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[949,1127,1820,1846]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[218,1363,182,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[208,1379,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Macuxi tunamore gen. nov. sp. nov. imago. A. male, dorsal view; B male, lateral view; C. female, ventral view; D. female, dorsal view; E. male forewing; F. female forewing; G. male genitalia, ventral view; H. detail of posterior margin of subgenital plate (ventral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3629084" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3629084/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="129">Figs 2A and 2B</figureCitation>
) black. Legs whitish. Forewing with whitish veins; stigmatic area with three cross veins not reaching subcostal vein; marginal intercalary veins paired, absent between IMP1 and A. Hind wing absent. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[862,979,1891,1918]" pageId="2" pageNumber="129">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[996,1179,1892,1918]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[218,1363,182,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[208,1379,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Macuxi tunamore gen. nov. sp. nov. imago. A. male, dorsal view; B male, lateral view; C. female, ventral view; D. female, dorsal view; E. male forewing; F. female forewing; G. male genitalia, ventral view; H. detail of posterior margin of subgenital plate (ventral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3629084" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3629084/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="129">Figs 2A and 2B</figureCitation>
) with terga and sterna I–VI white, VII–X brown; tracheation black. Caudal filaments lost. Genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[1027,1207,1928,1954]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[218,1363,182,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[208,1379,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Macuxi tunamore gen. nov. sp. nov. imago. A. male, dorsal view; B male, lateral view; C. female, ventral view; D. female, dorsal view; E. male forewing; F. female forewing; G. male genitalia, ventral view; H. detail of posterior margin of subgenital plate (ventral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3629084" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3629084/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="129">Figs 2G and 2H</figureCitation>
) with forceps black. Posterior margin of styliger projected ventrally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1675,2026]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1436,152,287]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="130" pageId="2" pageNumber="129">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,375,1999,2026]" pageId="2" pageNumber="129">Female imago.</emphasis>
Length: Body 
<quantity box="[549,627,2000,2026]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="2" pageNumber="129" unit="mm" value="2.3">2.3mm</quantity>
(n=1). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[714,778,2000,2026]" pageId="2" pageNumber="129">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[795,884,2000,2026]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[218,1363,182,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[208,1379,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Macuxi tunamore gen. nov. sp. nov. imago. A. male, dorsal view; B male, lateral view; C. female, ventral view; D. female, dorsal view; E. male forewing; F. female forewing; G. male genitalia, ventral view; H. detail of posterior margin of subgenital plate (ventral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3629084" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3629084/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="129">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
) light brown. Scape, pedicel and flagellum light brown. Eyes black. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[375,464,153,179]" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[480,562,152,179]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[218,1363,182,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[208,1379,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Macuxi tunamore gen. nov. sp. nov. imago. A. male, dorsal view; B male, lateral view; C. female, ventral view; D. female, dorsal view; E. male forewing; F. female forewing; G. male genitalia, ventral view; H. detail of posterior margin of subgenital plate (ventral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3629084" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3629084/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">Fig 2D</figureCitation>
) light brown. Legs whitish. Forewing with whitish veins; stigmatic area with three cross veins not reaching subcostal vein; marginal intercalary veins paired, absent between IMP1 and A. Hind wing absent. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[299,416,224,251]" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[430,608,224,251]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[218,1363,182,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[208,1379,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Macuxi tunamore gen. nov. sp. nov. imago. A. male, dorsal view; B male, lateral view; C. female, ventral view; D. female, dorsal view; E. male forewing; F. female forewing; G. male genitalia, ventral view; H. detail of posterior margin of subgenital plate (ventral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3629084" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3629084/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="130">Figs 2C and 2D</figureCitation>
) light yellow, terga VII – X light brown. Terga and sterna with darker longitudinal marks in all segments.
</paragraph>
